```python
    try:
        return datetime.datetime.strptime(
            dt_str, _RFC3339_MICROS).replace(tzinfo=UTC)
    except ValueError:  # maybe nanosecond resoultion
        if not dt_str.endswith('Z'):
            raise
```

The lines after that are just trying to get the nanoseconds part separated from the `YYYY-dd-mmTHH:MM:SS` part:  they discard the `Z` as extraneous.

